      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage hikes are a complex issue, but for small businesses in low-cost rural areas, the impact can be mixed. While increased labor costs are a direct challenge, these businesses often benefit from lower overhead in other areas, which can help absorb some of the increase. Successful small shops in these environments usually manage this by optimizing staffing schedules and focusing on high-margin items. Ultimately, it forces a re-evaluation of pricing and operational efficiency.",
