    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, but it sounds a bit optimistic. isn't it true that for a lot of small shops, even a small bump in wages can be the difference between staying open or closing down? i've heard people say it's basically a death sentence for local businesses in towns where everybody's already struggling to make ends meet.",
